Author: jl777c#5810
Content: when people say "no news" dont they realize there has been a lot of news in the recent months with price barely moving, so this is pressure that builds until one day it is unleashed. My theory is that every good news that has no price movement will someday create price movement "without news". It is a delayed effect. Do people really think that big whales read some news and then in the next hour buy millions of dollars worth? The news needs to be processed and digested and this takes time, so this could just be the AWS news effect. Or maybe just a fat finger by a large huobi trader and all the recent good news has no value at all

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: also if you look at orderbooks, there really isnt that much KMD for sale until you get to much higher prices. so to establish a truly large position in KMD requires paying a big premium
